                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-03T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 3, 1948—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>828. Suggested revision para (2) Art III rural reconstruction draft agreement
                    (Embtel 987 Jun 2) approved by Dept and ECA with following exception: Delete
                    last part final sentence this para beginning “and of the official”. This matter
                    will be covered in para (1) Art V.</p>
                <p>Emb authorized present FonOff draft agreement as revised above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
